## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-102">ASP.NET 运行状况监视，用于管理已部署的 Web 应用程序的生产和操作人员。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-102">ASP.NET health monitoring allows production and operations staff to manage  deployed Web applications.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-103"><xref:System.Web.Management>命名空间包含负责打包应用程序运行状况状态数据和负责处理此数据提供程序类型的运行状况事件类型。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-103">The <xref:System.Web.Management> namespace contains the health event types responsible for packaging application health-status data and the provider types responsible for processing this data.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-104">它还包含在管理运行状况事件期间帮助的支持类型。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-104">It also contains supporting types that help during the management of health events.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-105">此类不适于在您的代码中使用。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-105">This class is not intended to be used from your code.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-106">它是创建、 配置和 ASP.NET 运行状况监视系统用于通过电子邮件发送事件通知。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-106">It is created, configured and used by the ASP.NET health-monitoring system to send event notifications by email.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-107">可以在配置文件中，定义为事件提供程序，如本主题的示例部分中所示。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-107">You can define an event provider in a configuration file, as demonstrated in the Example section of this topic.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-108">此提供程序具有一组全面的配置属性，可用于自定义它的工作的方式。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-108">This provider has a comprehensive set of configuration attributes that you can use to customize the way it works.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-109">下面的配置文件摘录演示如何指定类型的提供程序<xref:System.Web.Management.SimpleMailWebEventProvider>中`healthMonitoring`部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-109">The following configuration file excerpt shows how to specify a provider of type <xref:System.Web.Management.SimpleMailWebEventProvider> in the `healthMonitoring` section.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9ba0c-110">`add`中的元素`rules`部分，指定提供程序将处理请求处理错误和基础结构错误。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9ba0c-110">The `add` elements in the `rules` section specify that the provider will handle request-processing errors and infrastructure errors.</span></span>  
  
```  
<healthMonitoring  
    enabled="true"  
    heartBeatInterval="0">  
    <bufferModes>  
        <add name="Critical Notification"  
            maxBufferSize="100"  
            maxFlushSize="20"  
            urgentFlushThreshold="1"  
            regularFlushInterval="Infinite"  
            urgentFlushInterval="00:01:00"  
            maxBufferThreads="1"  
        />  
    </bufferModes>  
    <providers>  
        <add name="CriticalMailEventProvider"  
            type="System.Web.Management.SimpleMailWebEventProvider,   
              System.Web, Version=%ASSEMBLY_VERSION%, Culture=neutral,   
              PublicKeyToken=%MICROSOFT_PUBLICKEY%"  
            from="sender address"  
            to="someone@example.com"   
            cc="someone@example.com  
            bcc="someone@example.com"  
            priority="High"  
            bodyHeader="Warning!"  
            bodyFooter="Please investigate ASAP."  
            subjectPrefix="Action required."  
            buffer="true"  
            bufferMode="Critical Notification"  
            maxEventLength="4096"  
            maxSize="4096"  
            maxMessagesPerNotification="1"  
        />  
    </providers>  
    <eventMappings>  
        <add name="Request Processing Events"  
            type="System.Web.Management.WebRequestEvent, System.Web,   
              Version=%ASSEMBLY_VERSION%, Culture=neutral,   
              PublicKeyToken=%MICROSOFT_PUBLICKEY%"   
        />  
        <add name="Infrastructure Errors"  
            type="System.Web.Management.WebErrorEvent, System.Web,   
              Version=%ASSEMBLY_VERSION%, Culture=neutral,   
              PublicKeyToken=%MICROSOFT_PUBLICKEY%"   
        />  
    </eventMappings>  
    <profiles>  
        <add name="Default"  
            minInstances="1"  
            maxLimit="Infinite"  
            minInterval="00:10:00"  
        />  
        <add name="Critical"  
            minInstances="1"  
            maxLimit="1024"  
            minInterval="00:00:00"  
        />  
    </profiles>  
    <rules>  
        <add name="Request Processing Errors"  
            eventName="Request Processing Errors"  
            provider="CriticalMailEventProvider"  
            profile="Default"  
        />  
        <add name="Infrastructure Notifications"  
            eventName="Infrastructure Errors"  
            provider="CriticalMailEventProvider"  
            profile="Critical"  
        />  
   </rules>  
</healthMonitoring>   
```  
  
